
Description
This repository contains multiple small Java applications showcasing object-oriented programming and exception handling concepts.
1. Mechanic and Employee System
•	Models a workplace with employees (Manager, Worker, TeamLead, Mechanic) and vehicles.
•	Demonstrates OOP concepts: classes, inheritance, encapsulation, and polymorphism.
•	Main class: MechanicApp.java
2. Password Validation
•	Validates user-entered passwords.
•	Uses a custom exception (PasswordVerifyException.java) to enforce rules.
•	Main class: PasswordValidationApp.java
3. Division Application
•	Performs integer division between two numbers.
•	Handles division by zero using exception handling.
•	Main class: DivisionApp.java
4. Battle Application
•	Simulates a simple battle between contenders using abilities like Water.
•	Demonstrates OOP with custom classes (Contender, Water).
•	Main class: BattleApp.java

Requirements
•	Java Development Kit (JDK) 17 or higher
•	IntelliJ IDEA (Community or Ultimate Edition)

Running in IntelliJ IDEA
1.	Open IntelliJ IDEA.
o	Go to File > New > Project from Existing Sources...
o	Select the folder containing these .java files.
2.	Configure JDK.
o	Choose Java SDK 17 or higher.
3.	Mark the source folder.
o	Right-click the folder with .java files → Mark Directory as > Sources Root.
4.	Run the desired application.
o	Open one of the main files (MechanicApp.java, PasswordValidationApp.java, DivisionApp.java, BattleApp.java).
o	Right-click → Run 'ClassName.main()'.

